            <div class="col-md-6">

                <h3>Summer</h3>

                <h5>Amanda Merritt</h5>

                <br>

                <p>Summer has been pinched at the wick.<br>
                Ribbons of cumulonimbus curl<br>
                all the way down the coast.<br>
                The sun steps into the hills<br>
                like a skipped stone<br>
                where colours leach<br>
                into the water table.<br>
                On the crest of the ridge,<br>
                a gull cries at the wind<br>
                about her stolen eggs;<br>
                you kneel quiet in your garden,<br>
                woven sweater and slacks grey<br>
                as the world that you tend<br>
                except for your hands, lit beneath the skin,<br>
                harvesting white roses.</p>

            </div>
